[30;1m160 | [0m[35m        # one utterance at a time[0m
[30;1m161 | [0m[35m        self.eval()[0m
[30;1m162 | [0m[35m        x = x.exp().transpose(-1, -2)[0m
[30;1m163 | [0m[35m        x = self.inv_mel_transform(x)[0m
[30;1m164 | [0m[35m        x = self.gl_transform(x)[0m

[30;1m15 | [0m[35m    Returns list of utf-8 byte and a corresponding list of unicode strings.[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35m    The reversible bpe codes work on unicode strings.[0m
[30;1m17 | [0m[35m    This means you need a large # of unicode characters in your vocab if you want to avoid UNKs.[0m
[30;1m18 | [0m[35m    When you're at something like a 10B token dataset you end up needing around 5K for decent covera[0m
[30;1m19 | [0m[35m    This is a signficant percentage of your normal, say, 32K bpe vocab.[0m
[30;1m20 | [0m[35m    To avoid that, we want lookup tables between utf-8 bytes and unicode strings.[0m
[30;1m21 | [0m[35m    And avoids mapping to whitespace/control characters the bpe code barfs on.[0m

[30;1m18 | [0m[35mclass FairseqIncrementalDecoder(FairseqDecoder):[0m
[30;1m19 | [0m[35m    """Base class for incremental decoders.[0m
[30;1m20 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m21 | [0m[35m    Incremental decoding is a special mode at inference time where the Model[0m
[30;1m22 | [0m[35m    only receives a single timestep of input corresponding to the previous[0m
[30;1m23 | [0m[35m    output token (for teacher forcing) and must produce the next output[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m    *incrementally*. Thus the model must cache any long-term state that is[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m2094[0m[34m of [0m[33m2691[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000610[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Linux[0m

[30;1m176 | [0m[35m            # a Python float, we roughly assume that if it's a tensor then it's[0m
[30;1m177 | [0m[35m            # probably not =1.0 anymore and we do the multiplication. Otherwise[0m

[30;1m37 | [0m[35m```bash[0m
[30;1m38 | [0m[35mwget -O gpt2_bpe/dict.txt https://dl.fbaipublicfiles.com/fairseq/gpt2_bpe/dict.txt[0m

[30;1m40 | [0m[35m    --only-source \[0m
